+# ADR-0002 — Three parallel-isolatable pure-utility modules in `src/lib`
+
+- **Status:** Accepted (Implemented)
+- **Date:** 2026-05-27
+- **Driver:** Idea — "add three independent, non-overlapping pure-utility modules to `src/lib`, each in its own new file with its own unit tests, sharing no files so they can be implemented fully in parallel."
+- **Author:** Solution Architect (T)
+- **Relates to:** [[ADR-0001]] (test harness + pure-logic coverage) — this ADR reuses that runner verbatim.
+
+## Context
+
+`src/lib/` currently holds two pure, dependency-free helpers (`cn.ts`,
+`format.ts`). The project is Next.js 16 / React 19 / TS-strict, ESM
+(`"type": "module"`). ADR-0001 established the test convention: `node --test`
+driven through `tsx`, colocated `*.test.ts`, extensionless relative imports
+(strict `tsc` rejects `.ts` extensions — TS5097).
+
+The request asks for three new utilities, explicitly designed to be
+**file-disjoint** so they can be built in parallel worktrees and merged with no
+conflicts:
+
+1. `src/lib/slug.ts` — `slugify(text)`
+2. `src/lib/num.ts` — `clamp(value, min, max)`, `roundTo(value, decimals)`
+3. `src/lib/str.ts` — `truncate(text, max, ellipsis="…")`, `titleCase(text)`
+
+These fit the existing `src/lib` convention exactly (pure functions, no
+side-effects, no cross-imports) — no architectural tension. The only shared
+surface is `package.json` (the `test` script + `tsx` devDep, owned by ADR-0001),
+which is a one-time wiring, not a per-module file.
+
+## Decision
+
+- Add each module as its own file with a colocated `*.test.ts`. **No module
+  imports another**, so the three tasks touch disjoint file sets and merge
+  cleanly from independent worktrees. The only shared edit is `package.json`
+  (test harness), done once.
+- Edge-case contracts pinned by tests (not happy-path only):
+  - **`slugify`** — lowercase → trim → collapse `[^a-z0-9]+` runs to a single
+    `-` → strip leading/trailing `-`. ASCII-only: non-ASCII letters (`é`) become
+    separators by design; documented and tested. Empty/all-separator → `""`.
+    Idempotent.
+  - **`clamp`** — inclusive bounds; `±Infinity` snaps to a bound; `NaN` value
+    propagates as `NaN`; `min > max` or a `NaN` bound throws `RangeError`.
+  - **`roundTo`** — exponential re-parse to dodge binary-FP artifacts
+    (`roundTo(1.005, 2) === 1.01`); non-finite value returned unchanged;
+    non-finite/negative `decimals` treated as `0`.
+  - **`truncate`** — counts the ellipsis against `max` (result length ≤ `max`
+    when `max ≥ ellipsis.length`); text within budget returned unchanged;
+    `max ≤ 0` → just the ellipsis; custom ellipsis supported.
+  - **`titleCase`** — capitalize first char of each `\S+` word, lowercase the
+    rest, **preserve original whitespace runs**.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- **Positive:** Three reusable, tested helpers; suite grows by 31 tests with no
+  new framework surface. The file-disjoint design proven — parallel
+  implementation/merge is conflict-free outside the single `package.json` edit.
+- **Cost:** None beyond the modules. `tsx` devDep + `test` script were already
+  the ADR-0001 plan; this run also wired them (workspace had reset to no `test`
+  script / `tsx` absent from `package.json`).
+- **Scope boundary:** `slugify` is intentionally ASCII-only (no diacritic
+  transliteration). If SEO slugs ever need `café → cafe`, that is a new task
+  (Unicode NFKD normalization), not a silent change here.
+
+## Task breakdown (3 parallel tasks · 6 story points)
+
+| # | Task | File set (disjoint) | Pts | Status |
+|---|------|--------------------|-----|--------|
+| 1 | `slugify` | `src/lib/slug.ts` + `src/lib/slug.test.ts` | 2 | done |
+| 2 | `clamp` + `roundTo` | `src/lib/num.ts` + `src/lib/num.test.ts` | 2 | done |
+| 3 | `truncate` + `titleCase` | `src/lib/str.ts` + `src/lib/str.test.ts` | 2 | done |
+| — | Harness wiring (one-time, shared) | `package.json` (`test` script + `tsx`) | — | done |
+
+**Verification:** `npm test` → 31 pass / 0 fail (~259 ms, Node v24.12.0);
+`tsc --noEmit` clean.
+
+**Verdict:** Change fits the architecture cleanly. Implemented and green.
